                            <comment id="240747" author="tappro" created="Sat, 26 Jan 2019 21:46:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, I working exactly on that&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="240745" author="bzzz" created="Sat, 26 Jan 2019 19:42:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;AFAIU, Mike has been integrating FMD code into the target thing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="240744" author="adilger" created="Sat, 26 Jan 2019 19:40:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Based on comments on Alex&apos;s last patch, the DoM code is not handling the file modification data (FMD) as is done in ofd. That tracks recent RPCs on each object and drops the modification time from writes that were generated before (lower XID) than setattr. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="240740" author="gerrit" created="Sat, 26 Jan 2019 10:48:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alex Zhuravlev (bzzz@whamcloud.com) uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/34115&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/34115&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
