                            <comment id="239975" author="tappro" created="Tue, 15 Jan 2019 10:54:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;test does the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Process #1: multiop oO_RDWR:w2097152_c
Process #2: wait #1 pause; setattr(mtime)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It works as expected when &lt;tt&gt;setattr&lt;/tt&gt; is being issued after &lt;tt&gt;write&lt;/tt&gt; and before &lt;tt&gt;close&lt;/tt&gt; as expected but sometimes it happens that &lt;tt&gt;write&lt;/tt&gt; is not flushed yet and this bug occurs . It can be reproduced with changing &lt;tt&gt;multiop&lt;/tt&gt; parameters as &lt;tt&gt;oO_RDWR:_w2097152c&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d propose to make sure that write is finished by doing data sync with &apos;Y&apos; parameter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
